        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 11:58PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1158 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Pelham to 7 miles southeast of Tannehill
Ironworks State Park to near Low Gap. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hoover, Alabaster, Pelham, Helena, Calera, Chelsea, Montevallo,
Brent, Columbiana, Centreville, Wilsonville, Indian Springs Village,
Vincent, Harpersville, Westover, West Blocton, Wilton, American
Village, Oak Mountain State Park, and Maylene.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for central, west
central and east central Alabama.</instruction>
